MIGHTY B! ♪

00:31.197 --> 00:33.199
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B! ♪

00:45.920 --> 00:47.630
[ping-pong ball clacking]

00:47.714 --> 00:50.800
[Bessie grunting]

00:53.553 --> 00:57.932
YES!
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM!

00:58.016 --> 01:00.018
[as Howard Cosell]
HAPPY HIGGENBOTTOM,

01:00.101 --> 01:04.022
{\an3}HOW DOES IT FEEL TO SUFFER
SUCH A CRUSHING DEFEAT?

01:04.105 --> 01:05.648
chomp!

01:05.732 --> 01:08.067
{\an3}HAPPY, COME ON,
NO HARD FEELINGS.

01:08.151 --> 01:10.653
{\an3}I'M SURE YOU'D BEAT ME
AT BUTT-SNIFFING

01:10.737 --> 01:11.696
{\an3}OR BONE-CHEWING
OR SOMETHING.

01:11.780 --> 01:14.491
{\an3}<i>BESIDES, THE BIG TOURNAMENT'S</i>
<i>COMING UP.</i>

01:14.574 --> 01:15.992
{\an1}[grumbles]

01:16.075 --> 01:18.661
{\an3}REMATCH, REMATCH, REMATCH,
REMATCH, REMATCH, RIGHT?

01:18.745 --> 01:22.081
{\an3}UGH, YOU CAN'T BE GOOD
AT EVERYTHING.

01:22.165 --> 01:23.500
OR ANYTHING.

01:23.583 --> 01:26.169
{\an3}PENNY, HAPPY'S
AN EXCELLENT BUTT-SNIFFER.

01:29.214 --> 01:30.423
OH, YOU BELIEVE THAT?

01:30.507 --> 01:31.758
HIPPIE'S IN THE FIRST ROUND
TOMORROW.

01:31.841 --> 01:32.717
CAKE.

01:32.801 --> 01:35.094
{\an1}I WAS TALKING
ABOUT ME.

01:35.178 --> 01:37.055
{\an1}YOU'RE GOOD
AT EVERYTHING,

01:37.138 --> 01:41.100
BUT ME, I'M NOT GOOD
AT ANYTHING.

01:41.184 --> 01:43.144
{\an3}NOW, THAT'S
JUST RIDICULOUS, PEN.

01:43.228 --> 01:44.896
IT'S TRUE I AM GOOD AT MANY,

01:44.979 --> 01:47.607
{\an3}MANY, MANY, MANY, MANY,
MANY THINGS,

01:47.690 --> 01:48.525
BUT SO ARE YOU.

01:48.608 --> 01:51.528
NUH-UH, I'VE TRIED
ALL KINDS OF THINGS:

01:51.611 --> 01:54.364
LICKING FLAGPOLES;

01:54.447 --> 01:55.782
UH, THERE'S WASHING SOCKS;

01:55.865 --> 01:58.117
I TRIED TO HANDSTAND,

01:58.201 --> 01:59.410
splash!

01:59.494 --> 02:01.663
BUT I JUST--MY HANDS
CAN'T GET THE HANG OF IT.

02:01.746 --> 02:03.081
THEY JUST WANT TO SIT ALL DAY.

02:04.374 --> 02:06.876
{\an3}COME ON, PEN-PEN,
DON'T GET DOWN IN THE DUMPS.

02:06.960 --> 02:10.170
{\an3}EVERYONE HAS
A HIDDEN TALENT.

02:10.255 --> 02:13.383
{\an3}WE JUST NEED
TO FIND YOURS.

02:13.466 --> 02:17.053
{\an1}OKAY, THIS NEXT ACTIVITY
REQUIRES SUPERHUMAN PRECISION,

02:17.137 --> 02:19.848
{\an1}AND I KNOW YOU'RE UP
TO THE CHALLENGE.

02:19.931 --> 02:20.890
ARE YOU READY?

02:20.974 --> 02:21.891
READY!

02:23.643 --> 02:26.604
{\an1}OKAY, PUT YOUR ARM OUT
TO THE SIDE.

02:26.688 --> 02:29.899
THEN CLOSE YOUR EYES.

02:29.983 --> 02:32.360
{\an1}THIS NEXT PART IS TRICKY,
SO BE CAREFUL.

02:32.443 --> 02:35.113
{\an1}BEND YOUR ELBOW
VERY GENTLY.

02:35.196 --> 02:35.488
THERE YOU GO.

02:35.572 --> 02:38.408
{\an1}AND NOW...

02:38.491 --> 02:39.200
TOUCH YOUR NOSE.

02:42.370 --> 02:43.913
<i>TOUCH YOUR NOSE.</i>

02:44.706 --> 02:47.083
TOUCH YOUR NOSE.

02:47.167 --> 02:49.168
{\an1}YOUR NOSE.
YOUR NOSE.

02:49.252 --> 02:50.253
{\an1}YOUR NOSE.

02:50.336 --> 02:51.170
UGH.

02:51.254 --> 02:52.171
{\an1}YOUR NOSE.

02:52.255 --> 02:54.591
<i>THERE YOU GO, PENNY.</i>

02:54.674 --> 02:55.592
{\an1}<i>JUST--</i>
<i>[sighs]</i>

02:55.675 --> 02:57.093
<i>PENNY, JUST--</i>
<i>JUST TOUCH IT.</i>

02:57.176 --> 02:58.428
<i>JUST--YOU'RE RIGHT THERE,</i>

02:58.511 --> 03:00.096
<i>JUST TOUCH IT.</i>

03:00.179 --> 03:01.264
FOR PETE'S SAKE, PENNY,

03:01.347 --> 03:01.723
IT'S RIGHT THERE
IN FRONT OF YOU.

03:01.806 --> 03:03.433
JUST TOUCH IT.

03:03.516 --> 03:04.601
OW!

03:04.684 --> 03:05.977
LET'S TRY SOMETHING ELSE.

03:08.605 --> 03:09.564
[gasps]

03:09.647 --> 03:11.399
crash!

03:12.650 --> 03:15.028
HOW ABOUT THIS?

03:15.111 --> 03:16.779
{\an3}ALL YOU HAVE TO DO
IS WALK FROM ONE SIDE

03:16.863 --> 03:17.989
TO THE OTHER.

03:19.824 --> 03:23.369
[electronic beeping]

03:23.453 --> 03:26.414
[suspenseful music]

03:26.497 --> 03:32.253
♪ ♪

03:32.337 --> 03:35.381
{\an1}[in slow motion]
HEY, PENNY.

03:43.890 --> 03:47.393
[Penny screams]

03:47.477 --> 03:49.979
crash!

03:50.063 --> 03:52.774
OKAY, HAPPY IS GONNA
PASS THE ORANGE TO ME

03:52.857 --> 03:54.192
UNDER HIS CHIN,

03:54.275 --> 03:55.193
AND THEN I'M GONNA PASS IT
TO YOU,

03:55.276 --> 03:57.862
AND THEN YOU PUT IT
IN THE BASKET.

03:57.946 --> 04:00.740
THIS SEEMS HARDER
THAN THE LAST ONE.

04:00.823 --> 04:02.367
OKAY, HAPS.
HIT IT.

04:06.996 --> 04:08.915
{\an3}YOUR CHIN.
PUT IT UNDER YOUR CHIN.

04:08.998 --> 04:10.541
{\an3}CHIN.

04:10.625 --> 04:12.502
[spits]

04:12.585 --> 04:13.711
[Bessie gasps]

04:13.795 --> 04:16.047
{\an3}I KNOW SOMETHING
YOU'RE GONNA BE GREAT AT!

04:18.423 --> 04:19.716
[grunting]

04:19.801 --> 04:22.470
THIS IS GREAT, PEN-PEN;
WE GOT A GOOD RALLY GOING.

04:22.553 --> 04:23.346
{\an1}I GET TO PRACTICE
FOR THE TOURNAMENT,

04:23.429 --> 04:25.306
{\an1}AND YOU GET TO PERFECT
YOUR NEW SKILL!

04:27.976 --> 04:31.437
[ping-pong balls clacking]

04:31.521 --> 04:34.482
I DON'T WANT
TO DO THIS ANYMORE.

04:34.565 --> 04:35.400
BUT YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

04:35.483 --> 04:38.403
{\an1}WE FINALLY FOUND SOMETHING
YOU'RE GOOD AT.

04:38.486 --> 04:39.153
I DON'T CARE.

04:39.237 --> 04:41.572
{\an3}IF THIS IS WHAT
I'M GOOD AT,

04:41.656 --> 04:42.615
{\an3}[spits]

04:42.699 --> 04:47.453
I MIGHT AS WELL JUST NAP
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE!

04:47.537 --> 04:49.038
{\an3}[screams]

04:50.623 --> 04:51.082
[thunder booms]

04:51.165 --> 04:53.710
CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

04:53.793 --> 04:55.044
"PUTT THE BALL, PENNY."

04:55.128 --> 04:56.921
"CROSS THE STREET, PENNY!"

04:57.005 --> 04:59.507
AH, DODO.

04:59.590 --> 05:00.883
[sneezes]

05:00.967 --> 05:03.553
[ping-pong ball clacking]

05:03.636 --> 05:04.929
[screams]

05:05.013 --> 05:08.808
[ping-pong ball clacking]

05:10.977 --> 05:12.562
HEY.

05:12.645 --> 05:15.440
[ping-pong ball clacking]

05:18.234 --> 05:20.153
YOU'RE DOING GREAT,
CHICKEN.

05:23.865 --> 05:26.784
[crowd murmuring]

05:26.868 --> 05:29.829
[back cracking]

05:32.623 --> 05:33.499
[breathing heavily]

05:37.003 --> 05:38.838
AS IT SHOULD BE.

05:39.922 --> 05:41.758
P. LEFKOWITZ?

05:41.841 --> 05:43.634
PENNY?
WHAT THE--

05:43.718 --> 05:45.970
{\an1}HI, BESSIE.
I ENTERED THE TOURNAMENT.

05:46.054 --> 05:48.222
REALLY?

05:48.306 --> 05:51.684
YOU KNOW WHAT,
THAT'S THE SPIRIT, PEN,

05:51.768 --> 05:53.227
{\an3}AND THERE'S NO WAY
YOU'LL COME IN LAST,

05:53.311 --> 05:54.937
{\an3}BECAUSE NOBODY'S WORSE
THAN BEN.

05:56.022 --> 05:57.523
[sniffing]

05:57.607 --> 05:59.692
{\an3}JUST HAVE FUN
OUT THERE!

05:59.776 --> 06:01.611
OH, BOY.

06:01.694 --> 06:02.361
{\an1}POOR KID,
SHE'S GONNA GET CREAMED.

06:04.697 --> 06:06.949
[upbeat rock music]

06:07.033 --> 06:10.828
[ping-pong ball clacking]

06:14.123 --> 06:14.957
{\an3}NEXT!

06:15.041 --> 06:18.086
[ping-pong ball clacking]

06:30.890 --> 06:33.518
{\an3}[screams]

06:36.104 --> 06:36.979
{\an3}GREAT GAME.

06:37.063 --> 06:38.106
{\an1}THE GOVERNMENT
USES COMPETITION

06:38.189 --> 06:40.274
{\an1}TO KEEP US
FROM REVOLUTION.

06:40.358 --> 06:42.151
{\an3}WHATEVER.
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

06:42.235 --> 06:43.111
{\an3}I WIN!

06:43.194 --> 06:44.153
{\an3}[gasps]

06:44.237 --> 06:45.613
[man over P.A.]
IN THE FINAL MATCH,

06:45.696 --> 06:46.906
WE HAVE B. HIGGENBOTTOM
VERSUS P. LEFKOWITZ.

06:46.989 --> 06:48.324
{\an1}BESSIE,
DID YOU SEE?

06:48.407 --> 06:51.202
{\an1}WE'RE PLAYING TOGETHER
IN THE FINALS.

06:51.285 --> 06:52.662
CAN YOU BELIEVE IT?

06:52.745 --> 06:54.080
{\an3}UH, NO.

06:54.163 --> 06:55.540
{\an3}DID SOMEONE
CRACK THEIR HEAD OPEN?

06:55.623 --> 06:57.834
{\an1}NO,
I FOUND MY TALENT.

06:57.917 --> 06:58.334
{\an3}SPRAINED
THEIR ANKLE?

06:58.417 --> 07:00.670
I'M JUST A NATURAL,

07:00.753 --> 07:03.172
{\an1}AND NOW WE GET
TO PLAY TOGETHER.

07:03.256 --> 07:04.173
[clicks tongue]

07:04.257 --> 07:06.843
SEE YOU OUT THERE.

07:06.926 --> 07:08.511
[cheers and applause]

07:12.098 --> 07:14.684
SHAKE HANDS, LADIES.

07:14.767 --> 07:16.144
{\an3}LISTEN, PEN,
I JUST WANT TO SAY,

07:16.227 --> 07:18.938
{\an3}WHATEVER
INEVITABLY HAPPENS,

07:19.021 --> 07:20.648
{\an3}YOU SHOULDN'T FEEL BAD
ABOUT LOSING.

07:20.731 --> 07:21.399
YOU'LL ALWAYS
BE ABLE TO SAY

07:21.482 --> 07:23.860
{\an3}THAT YOU STOOD
ON CENTER COURT.

07:23.943 --> 07:28.197
THE STUDENT HAS BECOME
THE MASTER, BESSIE.

07:28.281 --> 07:30.241
WELL, THAT'S A VERY HEALTHY
COMPETITIVE ATTITUDE.

07:30.324 --> 07:33.161
ONE THAT I WILL SMASH
TO SMITHEREENS.

07:33.244 --> 07:35.371
LADIES, PLEASE,
THIS IS NOT SOME DISCOTHEQUE.

07:35.454 --> 07:37.623
{\an1}THIS IS THE SAN FRANCISCO
PING-PONG CLUB.

07:39.625 --> 07:42.795
POOR SPORTS WILL BE FORCIBLY
REMOVED FROM THE PREMISES.

07:42.879 --> 07:44.964
SO WATCH IT.

07:45.047 --> 07:46.382
BEST THREE OUT OF FIVE.

07:46.465 --> 07:51.596
AS CHALLENGER,
MISS LEFKOWITZ WILL SERVE.

07:51.679 --> 07:52.847
[choking]

07:54.140 --> 07:56.184
[tongue lolling]

07:57.810 --> 08:01.522
[intense rock music]

08:01.606 --> 08:02.940
[screams]

08:05.735 --> 08:06.819
HA.

08:06.903 --> 08:09.697
[ping-pong ball clacking]

08:14.202 --> 08:15.161
[saw buzzing]

08:18.915 --> 08:19.624
[bell dings]

08:22.251 --> 08:25.296
[ping-pong ball clacking]

08:27.506 --> 08:28.466
[grunts]

08:31.636 --> 08:31.969
{\an5}HA.

08:31.636 --> 08:31.969
[grunts]

08:32.053 --> 08:33.888
[bell dings]

08:33.971 --> 08:34.847
{\an5}[screams]

08:33.971 --> 08:34.847
[bell dings]

08:34.931 --> 08:37.183
[both screaming]

08:37.265 --> 08:38.934
[both grunting]

08:39.018 --> 08:40.852
[grunts]

08:40.937 --> 08:43.105
HI-YA!

08:43.188 --> 08:45.816
[screams]

08:45.900 --> 08:47.902
[screams]

08:47.985 --> 08:48.986
[bell dings]

08:49.070 --> 08:49.737
[cheers and applause]

08:49.820 --> 08:51.614
AH, PLEASE,
YOU CLAP NOW?

08:51.697 --> 08:52.198
DID YOU MISS
THE LAST TEN POINTS

08:52.281 --> 08:54.367
I JUST WON IN A ROW?

08:54.450 --> 08:56.452
WATCH WITH YOUR EYES OPEN
AND YOU'LL SEE MORE.

08:56.535 --> 08:58.538
MANNERS,
MISS HIGGENBOTTOM.

08:58.621 --> 08:59.121
[chuckles]

08:59.205 --> 09:01.749
YOU GOT IN TROUBLE.

09:06.712 --> 09:07.630
[grunts]

09:07.713 --> 09:08.881
[intense rock music]

09:08.965 --> 09:10.633
crash!

09:15.513 --> 09:17.890
{\an5}[grunts]

09:15.513 --> 09:17.890
[screams]

09:21.227 --> 09:21.602
[laughing]

09:24.939 --> 09:26.482
[grunts]

09:26.565 --> 09:29.610
[grunting]

09:29.694 --> 09:30.653
[grunts]

09:30.736 --> 09:32.363
[screaming]

09:35.074 --> 09:37.493
[explosion, screaming]

09:38.744 --> 09:42.164
[screaming]

09:43.582 --> 09:45.293
[warbling noise echoes]

09:46.043 --> 09:47.753
crash!

09:49.505 --> 09:50.214
{\an5}[canon blast]

09:49.505 --> 09:50.214
[tuba blast]

09:50.298 --> 09:51.882
{\an5}[elephant roar]

09:50.298 --> 09:51.882
[tank firing]

09:51.966 --> 09:56.387
[explosions]

09:59.098 --> 10:01.684
ACE.
YES.

10:01.767 --> 10:05.313
HEY, THAT WAS OUT
AND YOU KNOW IT.

10:05.396 --> 10:06.772
CHALLENGE NOW.

10:06.856 --> 10:08.357
{\an3}CHALLENGE.
CHALLENGE NOW.

10:08.441 --> 10:09.358
WHAT?

10:09.442 --> 10:11.277
{\an3}WHAT, WHAT?

10:11.360 --> 10:13.529
{\an1}WHAT, WHAT YOURSELF,
BESSIE.

10:13.612 --> 10:14.405
OH, IT'S ON.

10:14.488 --> 10:18.909
DISQUALIFIED,
BOTH OF YOU.

10:18.993 --> 10:23.497
{\an3}SECURITY,
REMOVE THESE ANIMALS.

10:23.581 --> 10:25.583
{\an3}YOU'RE
UPSETTING MY STOMACH.

10:27.585 --> 10:28.127
[girls screaming]

10:28.210 --> 10:30.296
[both grunting]

10:30.379 --> 10:34.258
[both panting]

10:34.342 --> 10:37.636
[exhales heavily]

10:37.720 --> 10:39.889
I'M SORRY, BESSIE.

10:39.972 --> 10:41.432
ME TOO, PEN-PEN.

10:41.515 --> 10:43.726
{\an1}I SHOULDN'T HAVE DOUBTED
YOUR SKILLS.

10:43.809 --> 10:44.810
THE TRUTH IS,

10:44.894 --> 10:46.812
{\an1}YOU WERE PRETTY GOOD
OUT THERE.

10:46.896 --> 10:48.647
I WAS, WASN'T I?

10:48.731 --> 10:50.816
{\an1}YUP, AND I WAS GOOD TOO,
RIGHT?

10:50.900 --> 10:52.777
OH--OH, YEAH, SURE.

10:52.860 --> 10:54.445
{\an3}PRETTY--PRETTY GREAT,
BUT NOT BETTER.

10:54.528 --> 10:57.782
{\an1}WELL, TECHNICALLY,
I WAS BETTER,

10:57.865 --> 10:59.533
{\an1}'CAUSE I DID TEACH YOU
EVERYTHING YOU KNOW,

10:59.617 --> 11:00.242
{\an1}BUT YOU KNOW WHAT,
WHO CARES?

11:00.326 --> 11:02.745
LET'S JUST PUT
THAT BEHIND US.

11:02.828 --> 11:06.248
{\an3}GREAT, THEN LET'S AGREE
TO NOT TALK ABOUT IT ANYMORE.

11:06.332 --> 11:07.291
{\an1}NOT TALKING
ABOUT IT.

11:07.375 --> 11:09.168
{\an3}DEFINITELY
NOT TALKING.

11:09.251 --> 11:12.380
LAST WORD.

11:09.251 --> 11:12.380
WORD.

11:12.463 --> 11:14.090
WORD.

11:12.463 --> 11:14.090
WORD.

11:14.173 --> 11:15.091
WORD.

11:14.173 --> 11:15.091
WORD INFINITY.

11:15.174 --> 11:18.052
{\an1}WORD INFINITY TIMES INFINITY
TIMES A THOUSAND.

11:18.135 --> 11:19.512
{\an3}NOISES COUNT TOO.
[coughs]

11:29.772 --> 11:31.440
[people singing to the tune
of <i> Jingle Bells]</i>

11:31.524 --> 11:33.442
♪ TURKEY DAY, TURKEY DAY ♪

11:33.526 --> 11:35.444
♪ BUY DELICIOUS TREATS ♪

11:35.528 --> 11:38.072
♪ TURKEY DAY, TURKEY DAY ♪

11:38.155 --> 11:39.615
♪ EAT DELICIOUS MEATS ♪

11:39.698 --> 11:41.450
{\an5}(Portia)
YOU GUYS, THE THANKSGIVING
CLEARANCE SALE

11:41.534 --> 11:43.828
STARTED 15 MINUTES AGO.

11:43.911 --> 11:45.162
GIVE ME A BREAK.

11:45.246 --> 11:47.623
{\an1}THANKSGIVING IS NOT ABOUT
HALF-PRICE SALES

11:47.706 --> 11:49.959
{\an1}AND EATING UNTIL
YOU HAVE TO UNZIP YOUR PANTS.

11:50.042 --> 11:53.546
{\an1}IT IS ABOUT COMING TOGETHER
LIKE OUR FOREFATHERS DID

11:53.629 --> 11:56.799
{\an1}AND BEING TRULY THANKFUL
FOR EVERYTHING--

11:56.882 --> 12:00.428
{\an1}AND I MEAN EVERYTHING--
THAT WE HAVE.

12:00.511 --> 12:02.263
{\an3}I'M THANKFUL
FOR THE TURBO-3 HAIR-DRYER

12:02.346 --> 12:03.305
{\an3}I'M ABOUT TO BUY
ON CLEARANCE.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.474
[laughter]

12:05.558 --> 12:06.851
AND THAT IS WHY I PROPOSE

12:06.934 --> 12:08.769
WE SPEND THIS THANKSGIVING
HOW THE PILGRIMS INTENDED,

12:08.853 --> 12:15.651
{\an1}AT COLONIAL FARMS,
A THRIVING HISTORICAL VILLAGE.

12:15.734 --> 12:20.364
AT COLONIAL FARMS,
IT'S ALWAYS 1648.

12:20.448 --> 12:22.241
THERE'S HORSEBACK RIDING,

12:22.324 --> 12:24.201
CRANBERRY PICKING,

12:24.285 --> 12:27.121
SWIMMING WITH OTTERS,

12:27.204 --> 12:28.497
AND--WAIT FOR IT--

12:28.581 --> 12:29.623
NO PARENTS.

12:29.707 --> 12:30.833
[together]
AYE!

12:30.916 --> 12:34.670
{\an5}<i>(Bessie)</i>
<i>WELCOME TO COLONIAL FARMS,</i>
<i>BEES.</i>

12:34.753 --> 12:36.130
<i>WHEN WE PASS THROUGH</i>
<i>THESE GATES,</i>

12:36.213 --> 12:40.509
WE WILL BE TRANSPORTED
TO A SIMPLER TIME.

12:40.593 --> 12:41.469
UGH.

12:41.552 --> 12:42.511
{\an3}CORRECT.

12:42.595 --> 12:44.180
{\an3}THAT MEANS YOU MUST
LEAVE BEHIND

12:44.263 --> 12:47.016
{\an3}THE TRAPPINGS
OF MODERN SOCIETY.

12:47.099 --> 12:49.059
{\an3}YOU WILL ADDRESS ME
AS ELDER BAGG.

12:49.143 --> 12:51.729
{\an3}AND THIS IS MY WIFE,
GOODY BAGG.

12:51.812 --> 12:53.856
{\an5}<i>(Goody)</i>
<i>NO BEEPERS, CELL PHONES,</i>
<i>PAGERS,</i>

12:53.939 --> 12:56.192
<i>LAPTOP COMPUTERS,</i>
<i>DESKTOP COMPUTERS, MINI FANS,</i>

12:56.275 --> 12:57.526
<i>PORTABLE GAMING SYSTEMS, TVs,</i>
<i>PHONOGRAPHS,</i>

12:57.610 --> 13:00.237
<i>HAM RADIOS,</i>
<i>WALKIE-TALKIES,</i>

13:00.321 --> 13:02.114
<i>ROOM-TO-ROOM TELEPHONES,</i>
<i>OR OTHER ELECTRONIC DEVICES.</i>

13:02.198 --> 13:04.325
MY BRACES.

13:04.408 --> 13:06.660
[gagging]

13:06.744 --> 13:07.953
[gulps]

13:08.037 --> 13:11.040
[girls screaming]
NOOO!

13:11.123 --> 13:13.292
{\an5}DON'T DO THAT!
DON'T DO THAT!
DON'T DO THAT!

13:13.375 --> 13:15.503
{\an1}HERE'S TO
TRAVELING LIGHT.

13:15.586 --> 13:17.087
[laughing nervously]

13:19.423 --> 13:21.800
MAKE HASTE CHILDREN.

13:21.884 --> 13:24.053
{\an3}BARLEY PORRIDGE HARDENS
IF YOU LET IT COOL.

13:24.136 --> 13:25.763
YUCK.

13:25.846 --> 13:26.805
[gasps]

13:26.889 --> 13:27.389
[gobbling]

13:27.473 --> 13:30.559
AW, GIVE ME YOUR PAW.

13:30.643 --> 13:31.227
COME ON, PAW.

13:31.310 --> 13:32.311
PAW.
PAW.

13:32.394 --> 13:34.730
{\an1}PAW. PAW.
[laughing]

13:34.813 --> 13:37.483
{\an1}THESE WILL BE
YOUR SLEEPING QUARTERS.

13:39.693 --> 13:42.029
{\an3}NEWS FLASH,
BAGG,

13:42.112 --> 13:44.740
{\an3}I'M NOT SLEEPING
NEAR YOUR MOO COWS.

13:44.823 --> 13:47.743
HMM, PERHAPS YOU WOULD BE
HAPPIER NEAR THE SHEEP?

13:47.826 --> 13:49.203
[flies buzzing, sheep bleating]

13:49.286 --> 13:50.287
[laughing]
GOODY ONE, GOODY.

13:52.331 --> 13:54.083
{\an3}YEAH,
HILARIOUS.

13:54.166 --> 13:55.417
{\an3}THIS IS ALL YOUR FAULT,
MESSY.

13:55.501 --> 13:58.128
{\an3}WHERE'S
MY BATHROOM?

13:58.212 --> 14:00.839
AYE, THY CHAMBER POT.

14:00.923 --> 14:01.882
[flies buzzing]

14:01.966 --> 14:03.634
[laughing nervously]

14:06.637 --> 14:07.555
[shivering]

14:07.638 --> 14:10.599
[both grunting]

14:13.143 --> 14:15.854
[both grunting]

14:17.690 --> 14:19.191
YOU CAN HAVE
THE BLANKET.

14:19.275 --> 14:21.110
[shivering]

14:21.193 --> 14:23.070
SHH.

14:25.531 --> 14:28.158
[snoring]

14:28.242 --> 14:30.119
slurp!

14:30.202 --> 14:30.494
[screaming]

14:30.578 --> 14:32.705
[snoring]

14:34.582 --> 14:38.377
[rooster crowing]

14:38.460 --> 14:40.087
{\an1}RISE AND SHINETH,
PORTIA.

14:40.170 --> 14:40.462
[gasps]

14:40.546 --> 14:43.632
[moans]

14:43.716 --> 14:46.760
[off-key string music]

14:46.844 --> 14:54.727
♪ ♪

14:55.936 --> 14:58.856
[grunting]

15:10.743 --> 15:13.746
[saw noise]

15:22.838 --> 15:23.130
[both grunt]

15:26.425 --> 15:29.136
[retches]

15:29.219 --> 15:31.138
[cow moos]

15:38.312 --> 15:40.439
[grunts]

15:43.734 --> 15:44.318
[grunting]

15:44.401 --> 15:48.030
[exhales heavily]

15:48.113 --> 15:50.074
[grunting]

15:56.538 --> 15:57.164
[cow moos]

15:59.541 --> 16:02.586
{\an3}THE BLACKSMITHS MADE
EXTRA PUDDING JUST FOR YOU.

16:02.670 --> 16:03.879
{\an3}NUM, NUM, NUM,
NUM, NUM.

16:03.962 --> 16:05.214
{\an3}[laughing]

16:05.297 --> 16:08.092
I HEARD TELL SHE WAS MEANT
TO BRING FOUR PIES

16:08.175 --> 16:09.760
BUT NOW WILL BRING
BUT TWO.

16:09.843 --> 16:12.054
WELL, WHEN ONE
PAYS MORE ATTENTION

16:12.137 --> 16:14.473
TO ONE'S APPEARANCE
THAN ONE'S PIES--

16:14.556 --> 16:16.058
{\an1}WHAT?
WHAT HAPPENS?

16:16.141 --> 16:17.059
{\an1}THE PIES
GET BURNT?

16:17.142 --> 16:19.561
[women laugh]

16:19.645 --> 16:20.604
{\an3}[grunts]

16:22.022 --> 16:24.483
MY CUTICLES ARE SHREDDING.

16:24.566 --> 16:25.526
[grunts]

16:25.609 --> 16:28.278
{\an5}[screams]

16:25.609 --> 16:28.278
[all gasp]

16:28.362 --> 16:29.822
{\an3}OOPS.
[laughs]

16:29.905 --> 16:31.865
{\an3}SORRY.
[laughs]

16:31.949 --> 16:32.741
{\an3}SERIOUSLY,
SORRY.

16:32.825 --> 16:33.784
{\an3}[laughs]

16:35.369 --> 16:37.246
{\an3}I GUESS THEY'RE GONNA MAKE YOU
A NEW SUIT TO WEAR

16:37.329 --> 16:39.081
{\an3}FOR THANKSGIVING,
MR. TURKEY.

16:39.164 --> 16:42.000
{\an1}WELL,
HE'S GONNA HAVE DRESSING.

16:42.084 --> 16:44.336
AW, YOU'LL LOOK SO CUTE.

16:44.420 --> 16:46.588
[gobbling]

16:46.672 --> 16:50.926
{\an5}(Bessie)
NOW, THIS IS WHAT I CALL
THE THANKSGIVING SPIRIT, RIGHT?

16:51.009 --> 16:53.971
THE WHOLE TOWN
GATHERED AROUND THE BOG,

16:54.054 --> 16:55.764
PITCHING IN TO COLLECT
THE CEREMONIAL CRANBERRIES.

16:55.848 --> 16:58.976
{\an3}UM, CRANBERRIES COME
IN A CAN.

16:59.059 --> 17:00.436
LOOK INTO IT.

17:00.519 --> 17:02.938
{\an3}WHOA...UGH.

17:03.021 --> 17:04.522
[both chuckling]

17:04.606 --> 17:08.444
[screams]

17:08.527 --> 17:10.404
{\an3}PRAY CALM YOURSELF,
PORTIA.

17:10.487 --> 17:13.406
{\an3}YOU LOOK EXCELLENT
AS A RED-HEAD.

17:13.490 --> 17:15.659
WHEN WE GET BACK
TO THE 21ST CENTURY,

17:15.742 --> 17:17.411
YOU'RE DEAD.

17:17.493 --> 17:18.537
[grunts]

17:18.619 --> 17:20.539
[all laughing]

17:20.622 --> 17:23.208
{\an1}DEAD.

17:23.291 --> 17:25.252
DEODORANT, INVENT SOME,
'KAY?

17:25.335 --> 17:26.627
DEVIL'S FOOD CAKE.

17:26.712 --> 17:27.963
I CAN SEE YOUR PORES FROM HERE,
PEASANT.

17:28.047 --> 17:30.841
WHAT MANNER OF WICKED INSULTS
ARE THESE?

17:30.924 --> 17:32.968
[hissing]

17:33.051 --> 17:34.136
[all gasp]

17:37.556 --> 17:38.807
[gasps]

17:38.891 --> 17:40.058
THERE YOU ARE.

17:43.520 --> 17:44.897
[hair dryer blowing]

17:44.980 --> 17:47.649
[animals screeching]

17:47.733 --> 17:50.277
OH, YEAH!

17:50.360 --> 17:53.155
THAT'S WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT!

17:53.238 --> 17:56.366
MODERN TIMES!
YES!

17:59.870 --> 18:01.288
WITCHCRAFT.

18:01.371 --> 18:02.915
UM, I CAN'T HEAR YOU.

18:02.998 --> 18:06.460
HOLD ON, I ONLY HAVE
ONE MORE SECTION.

18:06.543 --> 18:07.795
crash!

18:07.878 --> 18:11.173
{\an3}WHAT MANNER
OF SORCERY IS THIS?

18:11.256 --> 18:12.341
THAT'S MY HAIR DRYER.

18:12.424 --> 18:16.428
{\an1}YOU'D KNOW THAT IF YOU EVER
WASHED YOUR HAIR, GREASEBALL.

18:16.512 --> 18:18.764
WHY, YOU LITTLE--

18:18.847 --> 18:21.183
[all chanting]
WITCH! WITCH! WITCH!

18:21.266 --> 18:22.768
[screams]

18:22.851 --> 18:25.062
[all chanting]
WITCH! WITCH! WITCH!

18:25.145 --> 18:27.648
[screaming]

18:27.731 --> 18:28.899
{\an3}WHAT'S GOING ON?
PORTIA?

18:28.982 --> 18:29.983
{\an1}PORTIA!

18:32.653 --> 18:34.863
{\an5}(Elder Bagg)
PORTIA GIBBONS,
THERE IS MUCH EVIDENCE AT HAND

18:34.947 --> 18:37.658
TO PROVE YOU GUILTY OF...

18:37.741 --> 18:40.202
WITCHCRAFT!

18:40.285 --> 18:40.994
[all gasp]

18:41.078 --> 18:43.497
I NEEDED A BLOWOUT,
BIG DEAL.

18:43.580 --> 18:45.999
[all gasp]

18:46.083 --> 18:47.334
SILENCE!

18:47.417 --> 18:51.088
DOES ANYONE HERE
SPEAK FOR THE WITCH?

18:51.171 --> 18:52.172
I DO.
I SPEAK FOR THE WITCH.

18:52.256 --> 18:56.552
I HATH KNOWN PORTIA GIBBONS
THESE SEVEN YEARS

18:56.635 --> 18:57.803
AND, YOU KNOW,
SHE JUST KIND OF LIKES

18:57.886 --> 18:58.887
TO DO THINGS A CERTAIN WAY.

18:58.971 --> 18:59.847
[gavel pounds]

18:59.930 --> 19:01.557
GUILTY AS CHARGED!

19:01.640 --> 19:05.060
{\an1}<i>SHE IS A GREAT</i>
<i>BIG WITCH!</i>

19:05.144 --> 19:06.520
TO THE STOCKS!

19:06.603 --> 19:07.771
[gasps]

19:07.855 --> 19:10.232
[all chanting]
WITCH! CONFESS!

19:11.525 --> 19:14.570
[gagging]

19:14.653 --> 19:15.612
[horse neighing]

19:15.696 --> 19:17.531
[chomping]

19:17.614 --> 19:19.408
[passes gas]

19:19.491 --> 19:22.202
[retching]

19:22.286 --> 19:25.205
{\an3}ENOUGHETH
IS ENOUGHETH.

19:25.289 --> 19:27.499
{\an1}DON'T WORRY, PORTIA;
WE'LL GET YE OUT OF HERE.

19:27.583 --> 19:27.916
{\an5}[turkey gobbles]

19:27.583 --> 19:27.916
[gasps]

19:28.000 --> 19:30.419
{\an3}MR. TURKEY.

19:30.502 --> 19:33.422
{\an3}[crying]

19:33.505 --> 19:35.757
NO!

19:35.841 --> 19:37.175
{\an1}[gasps]

19:37.259 --> 19:39.469
{\an1}ELDER BAGG,
I BESEECH YOU.

19:39.553 --> 19:41.430
STOP FOR JUST A SEC.

19:50.480 --> 19:54.151
[electronic beeping]

19:54.234 --> 19:56.570
{\an6}<i>(Elder Bagg)</i>
<i>LOOK, BRENDA, YOU PROMISED</i>
<i>THIS COLONIAL FARMS GIG</i>

19:56.653 --> 19:57.696
WOULD BE OVER IN THREE WEEKS.

19:57.779 --> 20:01.283
NEED I REMIND YOU I AM
A CLASSICALLY TRAINED ACTOR,

20:01.366 --> 20:02.159
{\an5}[gasps]

20:01.366 --> 20:02.159
<i>NOT A BABYSITTER.</i>

20:09.082 --> 20:10.334
LIES.

20:13.378 --> 20:13.670
[rooster crows]

20:13.754 --> 20:16.298
[moans]

20:16.381 --> 20:17.841
{\an1}<i>(Elder Bagg)</i>
<i>A RUSSIAN PLAY?</i>

20:17.925 --> 20:19.509
IN SARATOGA?

20:19.593 --> 20:21.261
BRENDA KNOWS
I CAN'T STAND CHEKHOV.

20:21.345 --> 20:25.933
WELL, RON, YOU COULD
ALWAYS SWITCH AGENTS.

20:26.016 --> 20:27.309
{\an1}UGH,
I NEED MY COFFEE.

20:30.228 --> 20:31.146
[all gasp]

20:31.230 --> 20:36.276
[all speaking at once]

20:36.360 --> 20:38.695
{\an1}<i>(Bessie)</i>
<i>YE LOOKING FOR SOMETHING?</i>

20:38.779 --> 20:40.030
{\an3}BUSTED.

20:40.113 --> 20:41.156
GET 'EM!

20:47.829 --> 20:50.540
ALL RIGHT, YOU LITTLE BRATS,
GIVE US OUR STUFF BACK!

20:50.624 --> 20:52.834
NOT UNTIL YOU APOLOGIZE.

20:52.918 --> 20:55.170
YOU CONDEMNED PORTIA
WHILST YOURSELVES STRAYING

20:55.253 --> 20:58.090
FROM THE IDEALS
OF COLONIAL FARMS.

20:58.173 --> 20:59.591
A VENDING MACHINE?

20:59.675 --> 21:00.133
FOR SHAME.

21:00.217 --> 21:02.010
WE'RE ACTORS,
KID.

21:02.094 --> 21:03.428
WHAT DO
YOU WANT?

21:03.512 --> 21:06.515
WE WANT TO EXPERIENCE
THE TRUE MEANING OF THANKSGIVING

21:06.598 --> 21:08.934
AS OUTLINED IN YOUR BROCHURE.

21:09.017 --> 21:10.852
UH, HELLO?

21:10.936 --> 21:11.812
OH,
AND OUR FRIEND.

21:11.895 --> 21:12.688
FAT CHANCE.

21:12.771 --> 21:15.649
[cell phone ringing]

21:15.732 --> 21:17.275
RON, YOUR PHONE'S RINGING.

21:17.359 --> 21:17.859
OH, LOOK,
IT'S YOUR TALENT AGENT.

21:17.943 --> 21:22.489
[gasps, grunts]

21:22.572 --> 21:23.824
LOOK AT YE.

21:23.907 --> 21:25.409
YE IS ADDICTED TO TECHNOLOGY.

21:25.492 --> 21:29.037
{\an6}(Bessie)
AND TO THINK IT WAS BUT
THIS VERY MORN

21:29.121 --> 21:32.040
<i>THAT WE WERE MORTAL ENEMIES.</i>

21:32.124 --> 21:34.793
<i>SURELY IT IS THE MAGIC</i>
<i>OF THANKSGIVING</i>

21:34.876 --> 21:36.253
THAT ALLOWS US TO COME TOGETHER

21:36.336 --> 21:39.464
AND BE TRULY THANKFUL
FOR EVERYTHING,

21:39.548 --> 21:42.551
EVERYTHING, EVERYTHING
THAT WE HAVE!

21:42.634 --> 21:43.385
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, RON?

21:45.929 --> 21:47.222
TOFU?

21:47.305 --> 21:49.182
[gobbles]

21:51.226 --> 21:53.854
